[SN]TITLE[SN]
Tesco and Burberry boost FTSE 100

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Shares in London were higher in early trading, with the benchmark FTSE 100 rising 0.5%.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Tesco rose 0.7% after UK competition authorities confirmed there would be an in-depth investigation into its proposed purchase of wholesaler Booker.
Burberry shares jumped more than 4% after it reported healthy sales growth for the three months to 30 June.
On the FTSE 250, JD Wetherspoon was up almost 2% after it said recent good weather had boosted sales at its pubs.
Premier Oil jumped 30% after it announced a "significant" oil discovery off the coast of Mexico.
On the currency markets, the pound fell 0.2% against the dollar to $1.2821 and was 0.2% lower against the euro at 1.1186 euros.
